{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":6104,"record_hash":"sha256:ca2a8c23798fff9c4a15dbe71313d33b41d58d029b37416e76d2164ce05bdcf2","timestamp":"2026-05-07T18:14:32.195Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 3b61f3\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1033\nOutput:\n# Agent Session Capture\n\nThis directory describes a proposed GitButler integration for capturing AI coding\nsession metadata into GitMeta.\n\nThis directory describes the current first proof of concept plus a parking lot\nfor ideas that are intentionally out of scope.\n\nBefore using this as a coding-agent prompt, run it through the review loop in\n[Spec Iteration Process](spec-iteration-process.md). For the first actual patch,\n[First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md) is the source of\ntruth.\n\n## POC Shape\n\nThe first milestone should be deliberately boring and explicit:\n\n- `crates/but-agentlog` owns agent log capture behavior\n- the GitButler CLI exposes a hidden, feature-gated `agentlog capture` command\n- the first implementation captures Codex data from an explicit transcript path\n- provenance/cursor data is written to GitMeta local storage by default\n- transcript envelopes are written only with `--include-transcript`, with a small\n  entropy/hex redaction guard applied before storage\n- no background watcher, broad machine scan, or remote exchange\n- GitMeta serialization and sync/push integration remain future work\n\nA good first command shape is:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture \\\n  --agent codex \\\n  --transcript-path <path> \\\n  --target project \\\n  --include-transcript\n```\n\n## Design Bias\n\nPrefer safety and auditability over clever discovery. It is better for the POC\nto capture nothing unless given an exact transcript than to accidentally capture\nthe wrong or private session.\n\n## Documents\n\n- [Spec Iteration Process](spec-iteration-process.md)\n- [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md)\n- [Requirements and Goals](requirements-and-goals.md)\n- [Architecture](architecture.md)\n- [GitMeta Data Model](gitmeta-data-model.md)\n- [Capture Workflow](capture-workflow.md)\n\n## Reference Material\n\n- [GitMeta specification](https://git-meta.com/spec/)\n- [GitMeta targets and keys](ht\n[TRUNCATED]\neys](https://git-meta.com/spec/implementation/standard-keys.html)\n- [GitMeta workflow guidance](https://git-meta.com/spec/implementation/workflow.html)\n# Capture Workflow\n\n## Hidden CLI Command\n\nThe initial CLI should be hidden and feature-gated.\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture --agent codex --transcript-path <path>\n```\n\nPOC options:\n\n```text\n--agent <codex>\n--transcript-path <path>\n--target <target>\n--include-transcript\n--dry-run\n```\n\nLater options:\n\n```text\n--agent <codex|claude|cursor>\n--session-id <id>\n--max-age <duration>\n--serialize\n```\n\n`--target` defaults to `project`; POC only guarantees `project`. Other explicit\nvalues may be passed through `git_meta_lib::Target::parse` only if directly\nsupported by public API.\n\nSerialization is not part of the first POC. It belongs in a later debug/sync\nmilestone with explicit privacy rules.\n\n## Capture Steps\n\n1. Parse CLI arguments.\n2. Require `--transcript-path` for the POC.\n3. Use the existing `but -C` / CLI repository resolution path. Transcript `cwd`\n   is validation-only and must not select the repository.\n4. Resolve the capture target, defaulting to `project`.\n5. Resolve the agent collector.\n6. Read transcript records from the explicit path.\n7. Read any prior GitButler capture cursor from GitMeta.\n8. Select only records that have not already been captured.\n9. Normalize selected records into JSONL-compatible strings.\n10. Write GitButler local-only metadata and cursor keys.\n11. Append local-only transcript records only if `--include-transcript` is set.\n12. Return a short command result.\n\n## Codex First Pass\n\nCodex stores session transcripts as JSONL files under a date-partitioned session\ndirectory. Records observed so far include:\n\n```text\nsession_meta\nturn_context\nresponse_item\nevent_msg\ncompacted\n```\n\nCodex records are adapter input. The collector should normalize best-effort\nfields into the shared transcript envelope (`session_id`, `provider`, `model`,\n`source_event_kind`, `turn_id`, `role`, `cwd`, etc.) while preserving the raw\nrecord as `source_record`.\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T18:14:32.195Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}